§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ In the English language, nouns are words that name people,
    places and things. ⦉

  ‖ In these sheets, names (see␣
    <a href='/sheets/names.html'>
      ‖ Names ⦉
    </a>
    ) serve the role of nouns. ⦉

  ‖ In the English language, verbs are words which talk about
    actions or relations. ⦉

  ‖ In these sheets, we use the verbs “is” and “belongs” for
    the objects discussed. ⦉

  ‖ And we exclusively use the present tense. ⦉

